## Experiment Complete: Stability-Channel GraGE Rebuild

### Result: **Primary Claim Supported**

**StabilityResidual-GraGE** is the first GraGE variant to consistently beat Feature-only with strong statistical support.

### Key Numbers

| Metric | Value |
|--------|-------|
| FSCC delta vs Feature-only | **+2.00 pp** |
| p-value | **0.0001** |
| Win rate | **0.87** |
| Cohen's d | **0.41** |
| LFS degradation | None (+0.73pp) |
| DAR degradation | None (+0.30pp) |
| Per-dataset: Cora | +4.43pp (p=0.0001, 10/10 wins) |
| Per-dataset: CiteSeer | +0.72pp (p=0.26, 7/10 wins) |
| Per-dataset: PubMed | +0.84pp (p=0.11, 9/10 wins) |
| Runtime ratio vs FO | 3.2× |

### What Changed

- **`src/grage/adaptive_score.py`** — Added StabilityResidual-GraGE method (5 new functions)
- **`scripts/run_adaptive_grage_search.py`** — Added stability_smoke/search/validate modes
- **`tests/test_adaptive_score.py`** — Added 7 new tests (all 24 pass)

### Method Summary

The method trains multiple GCN models with different edge dropout rates, computes per-node prediction instability (entropy, JSD, variance), converts to edge scores, residualizes against feature cosine, and optionally uses edge-gate gradient confidence as abstention. The stability signal is the primary driver; gradient confidence adds marginal value.

